# GSAP Animation Standards

- Prefer GSAP for animation instead of CSS keyframes.
- Use timelines for multi-step sequences.
- Use ScrollTrigger for scroll-based effects.
- In React, always clean up animations on unmount.
- Prefer refs, `gsap.context`, or `useGSAP` when working with components.
- Keep animations smooth and performant.
- Avoid animating layout-heavy properties when transform/opacity is enough.

## This repository

This project is vanilla HTML/JS. Reuse patterns from `gsap-utils.js` (`CampGsap` helpers, `ScrollTrigger` registration, `prefers-reduced-motion` checks) before adding new animation utilities.

```javascript
// ✅ GOOD — transform/opacity, ScrollTrigger, reduced-motion guard
if (!window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches) {
  gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);
  gsap.from(el, { opacity: 0, y: 12, duration: 0.6, ease: 'power2.out' });
}

// ❌ BAD — layout thrashing
gsap.to(el, { width: '100%', height: 'auto', top: 0 });
```
